cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CE, cs.MM

This paper discusses cooperative hybrid-ARQ protocols for wireless communication systems, which involve information theory, networking, and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
